--- mac os x ---

Building on mac:
git clone https://github.com/podofo/podofo.git
cd podofo

brew install fontconfig freetype openssl libxml2 jpeg-turbo libpng libtiff libidn cmake
mkdir build
cd build
cmake  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug -DCMAKE_FIND_FRAMEWORK=NEVER -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=`brew --prefix` -DFontconfig_INCLUDE_DIR=`brew --prefix fontconfig`/include -DOPENSSL_ROOT_DIR=`brew --prefix openssl@3` ..
cmake --build . --config Debug
sudo make install

This puts the libraries in /usr/local/lib, but executables produced by clang don't look there by default (??). The rpath stuff in LFLAGS in the makefile adds /usr/local/lib as a search path for dynamic libraries.



--- mingw on cygwin64 ---

The prerequisite libraries for building PoDoFo are available in cygwin64. You have to get the x86_64-w64 versions, of course.


cmake -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=x86_64-w64-mingw32-g++ -DCMAKE_INCLUDE_PATH=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/include -DCMAKE_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/ -DLIBXML2_INCLUDE_DIR=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/include -DLIBXML2_LIBRARY=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/ -DZLIB_LIBRARY=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/lib/libz.a -DFREETYPE_LIBRARY=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/ -DOPENSSL_ROOT_DIR=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/ -DZLIB_INCLUDE_DIR=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/include -DPNG_LIBRARY=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/lib/libpng.a -DJPEG_LIBRARY=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/lib/libjpeg.a -DTIFF_LIBRARY=/usr/x86_64-w64-mingw32/sys-root/mingw/lib/libtiff.a -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug ..

make -j 12

After all that, it doesn't work! Could be an incompatible version of openssl? ughhh

